Primarily endemic in the developing world where individuals acquire it from contaminated food and, especially, water, individuals visiting are at risk for typhoid fever. This is particularly true for VFRs, that is 'visitors to friends and relatives', where they are likely to partake of meals that may be contaminated with unclean water. 2 vaccines are available to prevent the infection, an injectable Vi antigen and an oral replication-limited Ty21a mutant. - Mod.LL]
